      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAPI ROCKS (5) is a progressive filly who made it two wins from as many starts this prep when she came from a similar barrier and got the cash by 2.2 metres at this circuit and distance. Fitter again so can continue her march through the grades. LEXUS LOU (7) did a good job to lead and score at the first run back from a layoff last time out over this distance at Newcastle, finishing one metre ahead of his rivals. Interesting to see what unfolds from a wider draw but he should strip fitter. SNIPERS FIRE (3) had a tough draw when she returned from a five-month spell with a placing at Young. Showed good ability last time in and draws much better so expect her to progress. HAS THE COURAGE (6) eases back in class so may be competitive.",
